<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Need help with Smithing</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Nietchze">Nietchze</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:03 p.m. 25/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Need help with Smithing<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>For the last week I have done practically nothing but Smithing. I am tired from all the damn Metal Bits I have made. I am tired of all the Skewer molds I have bought, not to mention all the water flasks. In a week's time, I have attempted to make over 300 Skewers, and have only made roughly around 15, but here is my dilemma, I have only gone from Skill 27 to Skill 45. Is that about right? I am roughly gaining 1 skill point in about 25 Skewer attempts. I have tried taking my shield and weapon out of my hands while making them. I have tried to wait while the servers didn't have as many people on them. How much do your Ability Scores mean to Smithing or is it all a random generated chance? I have spent almost 70 pp on Bits of Ore, water Flasks, and Skewer Molds. Any help would be appreciated. I am usually found around the Freeport area ( NRO, EC, WC, Oasis, and the city itself.)

<P>Numpsy, Cleric of Marr
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
